('Course Introduction, CSC838 - Artificial Intelligence', 'by Dr. F.A.U. Imuoukhome', 'CSC838 is an elective course and will be taken by Dr. F.A.U. Imuoukhome. \r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\nThis course focuses on; knowledge representation, reasoning and problem solving techniques, model of proof theory, natural language processing, and <b>A.I. programming with LISP and Prolog.</b>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\nA total of 5 students have opted to offer Artificial Intelligence this semester, however, no classes have been held at the time of this article. \r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\nBeginning on Friday, April 19, 2019, all students offering CSC838 are hereby informed that the class has now been fixed for <b>Fridays, 08:00 AM - 10:00 AM</b>. \r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\nFor more enquires, kindly contact <b>Mr. Harrison on 07066416750</b>.', 'ai.png', 'InformationAge.com', 0, '2019-04-19 08:00:00', 18),
('Lecture Note II, CSC824 - System Analysis &amp; Design', 'by Prof. (Mrs) F. Egbokhare', '<h3><b>System Development Life-Cycle (SDLC)</b></h3>\r\nThe System Development Life-Cycle framework provides a sequence of activities for a System Analyst to follow. It consists of a set of steps in which each phase of the SDLC uses the results of the previous step. The SDLC adheres to important phases that are essential for business processes. \r\n\r\n<h3><b>Systems Study Phase</b></h3>\r\nThe systems study phase is sub-divided into 3 tasks; \r\n<ol class=\"alpha-list\">\r\n    <li>Preliminary Study</li>\r\n    <li>In-depth Study</li>\r\n    <li>Feasibility Report</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>A. Preliminary Study</b></h3>\r\n<ol class=\"number-list\">\r\n    <li>System/Site Inspection - Involves going to the site to identify which processes need automation.</li>\r\n    <li>Observation - Identifying redundancies in the current system and how to automate them.</li>\r\n    <li>Terms of Reference (TOR) - Identifying the personnel in charge of certain processes in the current system.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>B. In-depth Study</b></h3>\r\n<ol class=\"number-list\">\r\n    <li>Problem Analysis - Identifying the problems of the existing system.</li>\r\n    <li>Stakeholders - Identifying the top management staff, external contractors and end-users.</li>\r\n    <li>Processes - Identifying the tasks, procedures and outcomes of the current system.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\nAt the conclusion of the in-depth study, a Terms of References (TOR) document must be produced. TOR defines the purpose and structures of a project, committee, meeting, negotiation, or any similar collection of people who have agreed to work together to accomplish a shared goal.\r\n\r\n<h3><b>C. Feasibility Report</b></h3>\r\n<ol class=\"number-list\">\r\n    <li>Areas of study - Stating the different parts of the organisation that was examined.</li>\r\n    <li>Objective - Stating the goals of the project and methods of achieving them.</li>\r\n    <li>Time - Stating the duration of the project.</li>\r\n    <li>Deliverables - Stating clearly defined outcomes/outputs of the project. Deliverables amongst all else, must be realistic and feasible.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>What is a Project?</b></h3>\r\nA project is a set of activities that ends with a specific outcome (<a>Egbokhare 2006</a>).\r\n\r\n<h3><b>Characteristics of a Project</b></h3>\r\n<ol class=\"number-list\">\r\n    <li>Project Planning.</li>\r\n    <li>Routine and non-routine tasks.</li>\r\n    <li>Tangible and intangible resources.</li>\r\n    <li>Distinct start and finish time.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>Components of Project Planning (S.M.A.R.T)</b></h3>\r\n<ol class=\"number-list\">\r\n    <li><u>S</u>pecific</li>\r\n    <li><u>M</u>easurable</li>\r\n    <li><u>A</u>chievable</li>\r\n    <li><u>R</u>ealistic</li>\r\n    <li><u>T</u>ime-bound</li>\r\n</ol>    \r\n\r\n<h3><b>What is a Business Process?</b></h3>\r\nA business process (BP) is a collection of inter-related events, activities, and decision points that involves a number of actors and objects that collectively leads to an outcome which is of value to the end-user or at least one customer.\r\n\r\n<h3><b>Life-cycle of a Business Process</b></h3>\r\n<ol class=\"alpha-list\">\r\n    <li>Process Identification</li>\r\n    <li>Process Discovery</li>\r\n    <li>Process Analysis</li>\r\n    <li>Process Re-design</li>\r\n    <li>Process Implementation</li>\r\n    <li>Process Monitoring &amp; Controlling</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>Business Process Management (BPM)</b></h3>\r\nBusiness Process Management is a body of methods, techniques, and tools used to discover, analyse, re-design, execute and monitor business processes. \r\n\r\n<h3><b>Business Process Modelling (BPM)</b></h3>\r\nBusiness Process Modelling is the activity of representing the processes of an organization so that they can be analysed, improved and automated. A systems Analyst uses BPM to represent a company\'s operations and information needs.\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n<b>NOTE:</b> BP Management and BP Modelling are both abbreviated the same way, be extra careful not to confuse one\'s definition for the other.\r\n\r\n<h3><b>Components of a Business Process</b></h3>\r\n<ol class=\"number-list\">\r\n    <li>Events</li>\r\n    <li>Activities</li>\r\n    <li>Decision Points</li>\r\n    <li>Actors</li>\r\n    <li>Objects</li>\r\n    <li>Outcome/Output (positive or negative)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>Definition of terms in Business Processes</b></h3>\r\n<ol class=\"number-list\">\r\n    <li>An event can trigger a set of activities and each activity requires time to execute.</li>\r\n    <li>A task is a single unit of work.</li>\r\n    <li>A task that requires many steps is known as an activity.</li>\r\n    <li>A process is a sequence of steps performed to achieve a given purpose. According to <a href=\"https://people.eecs.ku.edu/~hossein/Teaching/Fa13/810/Lectures/PA-chapter02.ppt\" target=\"_blank\">Pfleeger 2001</a>, a process is a set of ordered tasks involving activities, constraints and resources that produces an output.</li>\r\n    <li>A decision is a choice made from several options. </li>\r\n    <li>A typical process involves several decision points.</li>\r\n    <li>A decision point is a point in time in which choices are made that affect the way the processes are being executed. </li>\r\n    <li>An actor (also known as a performer) is an entity which takes care of a particular activity in a Business Process. Eg. Humans, Organisation, Software, Objects, Documents, Suppliers, Contractors etc.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<b>NOTE:</b> For examination purposes, Prof. (Mrs) F. Egbokhare mentioned that the definition of a process by Pfleeger is what is expected. And, when asked to define Decision Point, also state the meaning of Decision.\r\n\r\n<h3><b>Talking Points</b></h3>\r\n<ol class=\"bullet-list\">\r\n    <li>Feasibility Study in Systems Analysis</li>\r\n    <li>Factors affecting Information Systems success</li>\r\n    <li>Factors affecting Information Systems failure</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>Revision Areas</b></h3>\r\n<b>Dynamic Systems Development Method (DSMD)</b> <br/>\r\nDSDM is an Agile Project Framework and a generic approach to project management and solution delivery. It can also be applied in non-IT related projects.\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n<b>Define System Environment in relation to System Boundary</b> <br/>\r\nA System Boundary delineates a system from another system. The System Environment is the surrounding area outside a system. In most cases, the System Environment is not considered during System Analysis except when interaction between a system and its environment is being studied. Examples of such interactions are, exchange of; data, information, signals, energy etc.\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n<b>State 20 Facts Finding Techniques and write short notes on each.</b> <a href=\"media/uploads/downloads/20190423170000.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">[Download] 20 Facts Finding Techniques</a>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>Group Assignment</b></h3>\r\n<code>Identify an existing or proposed System at your place of work;</code>\r\n<ol class=\"roman-list\">\r\n    <li>Study it and model it as a Business Process. </li>\r\n    <li>Draw a <a href=\"https://www.brighthubpm.com/project-planning/12712-connecting-a-projects-parts-with-a-network-diagram/\" target=\"_blank\">Network Diagram</a> to show the activities and time stamps of the project, indicating time concurrences and dependencies where applicable.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<b>Submission date:</b> Tuesday, April 30, 2019. <br/>\r\n<b>Submission format:</b> Typed <br/>\r\n<b>Presentation format:</b> Group Presentation', 'bpm.png', 'HWP Labs', 0, '2019-04-23 08:00:00', 19),
('Class Updates - April 23, 2019', 'by Course Rep', 'Prof. (Mrs) F. Egbokhare, taking <b>CSC824 - Systems Analysis & Design</b>, has given us a grace period of one week  to submit the third assignment. The question for the assignment is detailed below.\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n<code>Get 3 journals on \"Problems of lack of user involvement in information system development projects\";</code>\r\n<ol class=\"roman-list\"> \r\n<li>Prepare a report on the above case study.</li> \r\n<li>Cite sources where applicable (E.g. <a>Egbokhare, 2013</a>).</li> \r\n<li>Include references at the conclusion of your report.</li> \r\n</ol>\r\n<b>Submission format:</b> Hand-written or Typed.<br/>\r\n<b>Submission date:</b> Tuesday, April 30, 2019.\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<b>CSC839 - Seminar</b> and <b>CSC831 - Operations Research 1</b> (Elective) did not hold today as the lecturer for both courses, Dr. S.S. Daodu, was unavailable. \r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\nThere was a group assignment given in CSC824, students who weren\'t around today should join Mr. Uyi\'s (<a href=\"tel:07034499753\">07034499753</a>) group to complete 5 members, and the rest students will be grouped on thursday immediately after the first class. Lecture note and details of the group assignment for CSC824 will be posted much later today. \r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\nAn example of <a href=\"https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conway\'s_Game_of_Life\" target=\"_blank\">Game of Life</a> algorithm explained by madam Oboro will be posted some time tomorrow in preparation for <b>CSC834 - Design &amp; Analysis of Algorithms</b>, which holds on thursday.', 'day_1.png', 'University of Benin', 0, '2019-04-23 16:00:00', 20);
