('CSC839 - Seminar', 'by Dr. S.S. Daodu', 'Below are the marks obtained by 10 students in Mathematics and Computer Science; <p></p>\r\n<table class=\"fig-table\" width=\"100%\" border=\"1\">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <th scope=\"col\">Students</th>\r\n    <th scope=\"col\">A</th>\r\n    <th scope=\"col\">B</th>\r\n    <th scope=\"col\">C</th>\r\n    <th scope=\"col\">D</th>\r\n    <th scope=\"col\">E</th>\r\n    <th scope=\"col\">F</th>\r\n    <th scope=\"col\">G</th>\r\n    <th scope=\"col\">H</th>\r\n    <th scope=\"col\">I</th>\r\n    <th scope=\"col\">J</th>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <th scope=\"row\">Marks (X)</th>\r\n    <td>43</td>\r\n    <td>62</td>\r\n    <td>45</td>\r\n    <td>39</td>\r\n    <td>41</td>\r\n    <td>50</td>\r\n    <td>70</td>\r\n    <td>65</td>\r\n    <td>50</td>\r\n    <td>55</td>                    \r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <th scope=\"row\">Marks (Y)</th>\r\n    <td>50</td>\r\n    <td>61</td>\r\n    <td>43</td>\r\n    <td>45</td>\r\n    <td>51</td>\r\n    <td>60</td>\r\n    <td>73</td>\r\n    <td>60</td>\r\n    <td>55</td>\r\n    <td>62</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<ul class=\"roman-list\">\r\n<li>Calculate the Coefficient of Correlation (r) using the Product-Moment Method.</li>\r\n<li>Is the Coefficient of Correlation (r) significant at alpha (&alpha;) = 0.05.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<code>\r\nTake (r) = &Sigma;(xy) / &radic;&Sigma;(x^2) * &radic;&Sigma;(y^2). <br/> \r\nWhere x = (X-Mean(X)) and y = (Y-Mean(Y)).\r\n</code>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<b>NOTE:</b> -1 &le; r &le; 1.\r\n<p></p>\r\n<b>Submission date:</b> Tuesday, June 18, 2019. <br/>\r\n<b>Submission format:</b> Hand-written.', 0, '2019-06-11 11:00:00', 21),
